   Findings - The results revealed that the farmers mainly selected farmers' market, cooperative, and wholesaler to sell their vegetables, which comprised 96.57 percent of total vegetable sales. Estimation results showed that cooperative, vegetable acreage, price satisfaction, and slow sales were most important factors which influence positively the probability of opting to sell vegetables at a cooperative rather than at the farmer's market. For wholesalers, gender of the household head and cooperative had most significantly negative effect, and age had a positive impact on farmer's choice of market channels.
